TITLE: ContextLoggerModule Configuration with Hooks (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure the ContextLoggerModule with hooks. It shows how to define hooks that run for all log levels and hooks that run only for specific log levels like 'error'. These hooks can be used for metrics, error reporting, or custom side effects. Note that hooks are executed synchronously and sequentially, which can introduce latency to the logging process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
ContextLoggerModule.forRoot({
  hooks: {
    // Run for all log levels
    all: [
      (message, bindings) => {
        metrics.increment('log.count');
      }
    ],
    // Run only for errors
    error: [
      (message, bindings) => {
        errorReporting.notify(message, bindings);
      }
    ]
  }
})
```

