TITLE: Configuring Jest Setup File (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet configures Jest to use the setup file created in the previous step.  The `setupFilesAfterEnv` option specifies an array of modules that Jest should execute after the test environment has been set up. This ensures that the ContextLogger is mocked before any tests are run.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "jest": {
    "setupFilesAfterEnv": [
      "jest-expect-message",
      "<rootDir>/../jest/setupFile.ts"
    ]
  }
}
```

