TITLE: Context Loss Due to Early Module Initialization (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This demonstrates a scenario where context can be lost due to initializing a module that depends on the logger before `ContextLoggerModule` has been initialized. Logs generated in `OtherModule`'s `onModuleInit` will not have the request context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
@Module({
  imports: [
    // âŒ Too early - logger not initialized yet
    OtherModule.forRoot({ 
      onModuleInit() {
        logger.info('Starting up');
      }
    }),

    // Logger module initialized after
    ContextLoggerModule.forRoot()
  ]
})
```

