TITLE: Piping Bootstrap Logs Through ContextLogger (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to pipe all NestJS bootstrap logs through the ContextLogger to ensure consistent logging format and integration. This is achieved by creating a `ContextLogger` instance and passing it to `NestFactory.create` during application setup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async function bootstrap() {
  const bootstrapLogger = new ContextLogger('Bootstrap');

  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule, {
    bufferLogs: true,
    logger: bootstrapLogger
  });

  await app.listen(3000);
}
```

