TITLE: Access Context in Service (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Example of accessing and using the logger's context in another service (FeatureService). The context, including userId and tier, persists from previous services.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
@Injectable()
export class FeatureService {
  private readonly logger = new ContextLogger(FeatureService.name);

  async checkFeatures() {
    this.logger.info('Checking features');
    // Output: {
    //   "message": "Checking features",
    //   "userId": "user_123",  // Still here from AuthGuard
    //   "tier": "premium",     // Still here from PaymentService
    //   ...other context
    // }
  }
}
```

