TITLE: Context Adaptation Configuration (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Configuration for adapting (transforming) the context before logging.  This example shows how to remove sensitive data, rename fields, and add new fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
ContextLoggerModule.forRoot({
  contextAdapter: (context) => ({
    ...context,
    sensitive: undefined,           // Remove sensitive data
    requestId: context.reqId,      // Rename fields
    timestamp: Date.now()          // Add new fields
  })
})
```

