TITLE: Context Loss in Background Operations (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how context can be lost in background operations or timers.  Since the `setTimeout` callback is executed in a new execution context, the logger will not have any context available.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adird/nestjs-context-logger/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// âŒ Context lost - new execution context
setTimeout(() => {
  logger.info('Task done');  // No context available
}, 1000);
```

